cs.CR, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.NI 

This paper deals with privacy-preserving mechanisms for spectrum auctions, which involves cryptography and game theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves optimization and algorithm design, which suggests categories such as cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper involves network communication and distributed systems, which suggests categories such as cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
